<inglise> COMMISSION REGULATION (EEC) No 815/89 of 30 March 1989 on the grant of refunds for coloured barley </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EM&Uuml;) nr 815/89 toetuste andmise kohta v&auml;rvitud odrale 30. m&auml;rts 1989 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 2727/75 of 29 October 1975 on the common organization of the market in cereals (1), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 166/89 (2), and in particular Articles 16 (6) and 24 thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 29. oktoobri 1975. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 2727/75 teraviljaturu &uuml;hise korralduse kohta (1) (viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 166/89 (2)), eriti selle artikli 16 l&otilde;iget 6 ja artiklit 24, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 2746/75 of 29 October 1975 laying down general rules for granting export refunds on cereals and criteria for fixing the amount of such refunds (3), and in particular Article 8 (2), second subparagraph, and (3) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 29. oktoobri 1975. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 2746/75, millega kehtestatakse teraviljale eksporditoetuste andmise &uuml;ldeeskirjad ning nende toetuste suuruse kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ramise kriteeriumid, (3) eriti selle artikli 8 l&otilde;ike 2 teist l&otilde;iku ja l&otilde;iget 3, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Article 4 (1) of Commission Regulation (EEC) No 3665/87 (4), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 3993/88 (5), provides that the export refund is to be paid subject in particular to proof being furnished that the product in question has actually left the customs territory of the Community in the unaltered state; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: komisjoni m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3665/87 (4) (viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 3993/88 (5)) artikli 4 l&otilde;ige 1 n&auml;eb ette, et eksporditoetuse maksmise tingimus on eesk&auml;tt t&otilde;endi esitamine k&otilde;nealuse toote lahkumise kohta &uuml;henduse tolliterritooriumilt t&ouml;&ouml;tlemata kujul; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas certain requirements of third countries require exporters to colour barley before it leaves the customs territory of the Community; </inglise>
<eesti> kolmandate riikide teatavate n&otilde;udmiste t&otilde;ttu tuleb eksportijatel oder enne selle lahkumist &uuml;henduse tolliterritooriumilt v&auml;rvida; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, in order to avoid divergences in the Community in the application of Articles 4 and 28 (4) of Regulation (EEC) No 3665/87, it should be indicated clearly that where barley is coloured in agreement with the customs authorities this does not affect entitlement to the refund for the product in question; </inglise>
<eesti> erinevuste v&auml;ltimiseks m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3665/87 artikli 4 ja artikli 28 l&otilde;ike 4 kohaldamisel &uuml;henduses tuleks selgelt &auml;ra n&auml;idata, et kui oder on v&auml;rvitud kokkuleppel tolliametnikega, ei m&otilde;juta see k&otilde;nealuse toote &otilde;igust saada toetust; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Cereals, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;rusega etten&auml;htud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las teravilja korralduskomitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> After prior notification to the customs authorities and in agreement with the latter, barley to be exported which is the subject of an export declaration as referred to in Article 3 of Regulation (EEC) No 3665/87 or a payment declaration as referred to in Article 25 of that Regulation may be coloured without the product's conformity with the provisions of Article 4 of the same Regulation and Article 5 of Council Regulation (EEC) No 565/80 (6) being called into question. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui tolliametnikele on ette teatatud ja nendega kokku lepitud, v&otilde;ib eksporditavat otra, mille kohta on koostatud m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 3665/87 artikli 3 kohane ekspordideklaratsioon v&otilde;i selle m&auml;&auml;ruse artikli 25 kohane maksedeklaratsioon, v&auml;rvida, ilma et satuks kahtluse alla toote vastavus sama m&auml;&auml;ruse artiklis 4 ja n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 565/80 (6) artiklis 5 s&auml;testatule. </eesti>
<inglise> In that case, the T 5 control copy referred to in Article 1 of Commission Regulation (EEC) No 2823/87 (7) shall be endorsed accordingly. </inglise>
<eesti> Sel juhul tuleb komisjoni m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 2823/87 (7) artiklis 1 nimetatud kontrolleksemplar T5 vastavalt t&auml;histada. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the day of its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas avaldamise p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise> It shall apply with effect from 1 January 1988, with exception of the obligation in Article 1 regarding prior notification. </inglise>
<eesti> Seda kohaldatakse alates 1. jaanuarist 1988, v&auml;lja arvatud artiklis 1s&auml;testatud kohustus etteteatamise suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 30 March 1989. </inglise>
<eesti> Br&uuml;ssel, 30. m&auml;rts 1989 </eesti>
